  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n87283bc\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nSee https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/5038#issuecomment-1751727791 and https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/5928#issuecomment-1751337269\r\n\r\nIt seems that this [commit](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/5928) broke this test case:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n  function test_parse_11e20_sci() public {\r\n    string memory json = '{\"value\": 1.1e20}';\r\n    bytes memory parsed = vm.parseJson(json);\r\n    Value memory data = abi.decode(parsed, (Value));\r\n    assertEq(data.value, 1.1e20);\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat passes as recently as this commit [7b291d4](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/commit/7b291d43778be31620a9b45b19a68339f7286f08)\r\n\r\n```\r\n(returns [PASS] test_parse_11e20_sci() (gas: 4124))\r\n```\r\n\r\nOn `87283bc`, this test returns:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[FAIL. Reason: Failed to parse key \"$\": Unsupported value: Number(1.1e20)] test_parse_11e20_sci() (gas: 3308)\r\n```\r\n\r\ncc @mds1 ",
